claim.claim-text:
1. A method of selecting one of a plurality of communications channel modes for a communications session initiated by a communications terminal, including: 
storing information relating to channel usage according to type of communications session; 
identifying the type of an initiated communications session; and selecting said one communications channel mode on the basis of said stored information relating to the type of the initiated communications session.

4. A method of selecting one of a plurality of communications channel modes for a communications session initiated by a communications terminal, including: 
storing information relating to channel usage according to type of communications session; 
identifying the type of an initiated communications session; 
selecting said one communications channel mode on the basis of said stored information relating to the type of the initiated communications session; and 
modifying said stored data on the basis of previous usage of said channel modes.

7. A method of selecting one of a plurality of communications channel modes for a communications session initiated by a communications terminal, including: 
storing information relating to channel usage according to type of communications session; 
identifying the type of an initiated communications session; 
selecting said one communications channel mode on the basis of said stored information relating to the type of the initiated communications session; and 
monitoring usage of said channel modes by the communications terminal, wherein information is stored relating to said monitored usage.

17. A method of selecting one of a plurality of communications channel modes for a communications session initiated by a communications terminal, including: 
storing information relating to channel usage according to type of communications session; 
identifying the type of an initiated communications session; 
selecting said one communications channel mode on the basis of said stored information relating to the type of the initiated communications session; and 
in which said type includes a communications application type.
